page.title: 04TYPICAL DAY
page.content: My cat wakes me up and another day begins.I jump out of bed,clean my teeth get dressed and go up to the table with the delicious smell of breakfast I have my breakfast about seven forty five every morning the same as other days.My cat it meows she is hungry too or does she want to get out in the fresh air? No answer to that she does as she pleases anyway.The first day of the summer term I go outside just like any other morning,how bright the sun is,the washing will soon dry in the warmth, what was that a spot of rain surely not this bright day then I realise I'm standing under the washing line .Drip drip.There is a pole that holds the washing,my cat is just like a monkey it climbs up it,the silly thing.A shout from the window,dinner is nearly
